      <description>&lt;p&gt;Design thinking is more than a methodology—it&amp;rsquo;s a mindset that helps solve complex problems through a human-centered approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Core Principles&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After working on numerous projects across different industries, I&amp;rsquo;ve found these principles consistently valuable:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;1. Empathy First&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Understanding the user&amp;rsquo;s needs, pain points, and context is the foundation of effective design. Before sketching or prototyping, invest time in research and observation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;2. Define the Problem Clearly&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A well-defined problem is halfway to a solution. Take time to articulate what you&amp;rsquo;re actually trying to solve.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
